{"TopicId":170996,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Starlink Thread (split from SpaceX)","CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-17T03:46:55Z","PageNum":26,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SunlitZelkova","CreatedById":206402,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-22T05:36:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224147230\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170996\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221655820975\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts losing control of the info-space within China.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile this is a problem (for them, to be clear), I don\u2019t think it is the motive behind their military counter-Starlink studies.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis could be countered on the ground by interdicting smuggling of Starlink terminals. That would be extremely difficult, but another option would be to set up some sort of system designed to detect Starlink connections. Have a sat in GEO above China listening, have it pick up Starlink signals, and then pinpoint the location so it can be forwarded to the police.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut a much more effective \u201Ccounter\u201D to that side of the \u201CStarlink crisis\u201D is the fact that revolution is hard. As has been proven over the last 80 or so years, it is one thing to know what is going on in the world, but it is far, far more difficult to do something about it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-22T15:00:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224147469\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170996\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221655876195\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206402\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SunlitZelkova\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, SunlitZelkova said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nrevolution is hard\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue - but information is power.\u00A0 Allowing the people to gain information, they may start asking questions and advocating for change.\u00A0 You don\u0027t need a full blown revolution to shift your government... Or even change it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut yes - Starlink is an easily interdicted terminal; all the military has to do is fly drones over the city and map the location and frequency of the emissions... Knock knock bang.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-29T20:49:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://api.starlink.com/public-files/BrightnessMitigationBestPracticesSatelliteOperators.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://api.starlink.com/public-files/BrightnessMitigationBestPracticesSatelliteOperators.pdf\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-30T01:22:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159228\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170996\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659127781\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://api.starlink.com/public-files/BrightnessMitigationBestPracticesSatelliteOperators.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://api.starlink.com/public-files/BrightnessMitigationBestPracticesSatelliteOperators.pdf\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, nice to see that they address this head-on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, the \u0027perspective\u0027 piece about altitude, with 1200km satellites being visible at midnight vs Starlink\u0027s low altitude.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-22T14:37:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.technologyreview.com/2022/10/21/1062001/spacex-starlink-signals-reverse-engineered-gps/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.technologyreview.com/2022/10/21/1062001/spacex-starlink-signals-reverse-engineered-gps/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-05T04:52:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://edition.cnn.com/2022/11/04/politics/spacex-ukraine-elon-musk-starlink-internet-outage/index.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://edition.cnn.com/2022/11/04/politics/spacex-ukraine-elon-musk-starlink-internet-outage/index.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-05T14:40:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s all about the shekels\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-05T15:08:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPaying for stuff you use is entirely appropriate. Items donated were already paid for (unless Raytheon retroactively gave the money back to the original buyers, LOL\u2014yeah, no).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-08T21:55:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed724172651\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/Starlink/status/1777441354588791206?t=0DShqZsrE4zmZZ-P6-CjRw%26s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:406px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}